am only available on Fridays? And then basically they're like, well, it's so complicated to deploy that they need to blah, blah, blah, blah, blah. So it's complicated. They're like, huh, well, why is it so complicated? Well, because we reimage the whole machine and we do this whole process, et cetera. And then maybe the next question is, why do we do that? Why don't we just do a different way that's easier? You know, and so so again, it's kind of this concept of of like not in trying to be necessarily controversial or trying to cause a conflict. But but let's get to the root of the problem and let's fix it so that every day we get better, every day we get better. And so I think the it may be related to that other concept as well. But to me, those Kaizen and five wise are very similar in that it's a great feedback loop to to make continuous improvement. you",
